House Resolution 153
By: Representatives Willis of the 55th and Jackson of the 165th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Helen Marie Richardson Louis; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Helen Marie Richardson Louis; and
4 WHEREAS, Helen Marie Richardson Louis was born on October 27, 1943, in Savannah,
5 Georgia, the beloved daughter of Joseph Richardson Sr. and Florine Rogers Strong; and
6 WHEREAS, she earned a bachelor's degree with honors in education from Savannah State
7 College before relocating to Atlanta, Georgia, to begin her career as an educator, later
8 obtaining a master's degree in education from Georgia State University and completing all
9 course work toward a Doctorate in Education at Walden University; and
10 WHEREAS, Helen Marie Richardson Louis dedicated 37 years of service to the Atlanta
11 Public School System as an elementary school teacher and school psychologist, where she
12 was entrusted with some of the most challenging classrooms, commanded the respect of
13 students and colleagues alike, and received numerous accolades for her outstanding
14 contributions to education; and
