15 WHEREAS, initiated into the Atlanta Alumnae Chapter on December 13, 1980, she was a
16 Golden Life Member of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated, where she co-chaired
17 several committees and offered mentorship to undergraduate members; and
18 WHEREAS, a woman of deep and abiding faith, she gave her life to Christ at an early age
19 at First Evergreen Baptist Church in Savannah and later became an active member of
20 Antioch Baptist Church North in Atlanta, where she participated in the CMA Bell Choir, the
21 Verse Speaking Choir, and the Usher Board; and
22 WHEREAS, Helen Marie Richardson Louis was a beloved mother, grandmother, and
23 matriarch, leaving behind a legacy of love and encouragement for her two daughters,
24 Quadralyn and DeVita, as well as her two grandchildren, Charles and Micala, whom she
25 adored and supported throughout their lives and accomplishments; and
26 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous woman, Helen Marie Richardson Louis will long
27 be remembered for her love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all
28 who had the great fortune of knowing her.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Helen Marie Richardson
31 Louis and express their deepest and most sincere regret at her passing.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
33 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
34 family of Helen Marie Richardson Louis.
